This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with natural language processing and classification of offensive content on Twitter. It may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it involves analyzing social media data. The use of ensemble classifiers and data enhancement methods suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) may also be a relevant sub-category as the paper deals with classification and retrieval of offensive content. Finally, Cybersecurity (cs.CY) may be a possible sub-category as the paper deals with identifying and mitigating offensive content on social media platforms.
